on to love it #4: 334-mile range RS model\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe base Chevrolet Blazer EV LT features a 283-mile range when equipped with AWD, but it\u0026#39;s the RS model that truly shines. The mid-level trim starts at $49,900 MSRP and features a 334-mile range on RWD models, making it the go-to Blazer EV if you want as much range as you can get. Note that switching to a rear-wheel drivetrain will cost you extra, though.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA3OTk5MzI5OTA0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev.jpg\" height=\"900\" width=\"1600\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJames Riswick\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThat 334-mile range puts the RS trim a step ahead of competitors. For example, the \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/honda/\"\u003eHonda\u003c/a\u003e Prologue features a maximum range of 296 miles, while the 2025 \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/kia/\"\u003eKia\u003c/a\u003e EV9 tops out with an EPA-estimated 304-mile range. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/news/honda-eyes-sub-30000-ev-for-u-s-market\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"reason-to-love-it-5-price-undercuts-competitors\"\u003eReason to love it #5: Price undercuts competitors\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe 2025 Chevrolet Blazer EV starts at $44,700, undercutting most of its main competitors. The 2024 Honda Prologue starts at $47,400, while the 2025 Kia EV9 comes in at $54,900. The 2024 Jeep Wagoneer S is currently among the most expensive models in its class, boasting a hefty price tag of $70,795.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4Mjc1NTY0MTQ0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-rs-badge.jpg\" height=\"900\" width=\"1600\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJames Riswick\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"reason-to-think-twice-1-no-apple-carplay-or-android-auto\"\u003eReason to think twice #1: No Apple CarPlay or Android Auto\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eApple CarPlay and Android Auto compatibility has become a popular feature among consumers. Unfortunately for the Chevrolet Blazer EV, GM decided to go with built-in Google native software, which includes apps like Google Maps.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eCompeting all-electric SUVs, including the Honda Prologue, come equipped with wireless Apple CarPlay and Android Auto compatibility.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDA4MjczMjcwMzg0/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-infotainment-double-map.jpg\" height=\"900\" width=\"1600\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJames Riswick\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/news/how-byd-is-conquering-the-global-automotive-market\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn an effort to break into the EV scene in a timely manner, Honda partnered with General Motors to create an all-electric model built on one of their platforms. As a result, the Honda Prologue and Chevrolet Blazer EV share the same battery and powertrain.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe two models don’t look anything alike when it comes to styling, but it’s clear the Honda Prologue is the consumer favorite. The 2024 Honda Prologue outsold not only the Chevrolet Blazer EV, but it landed a pretty decisive win. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Passenger’s side view of the 2024 Blazer EV SS in Radiant Red Tintcoat driving on a road with trees. Preproduction model shown. Actual production model may vary. 2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV available Spring 2023.\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MDg5MDkyNTU1MzE5MTQw/2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss.jpg\" height=\"2662\" width=\"4732\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e2024 Chevrolet Blazer EV\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChevrolet\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhereas the Chevrolet Blazer EV saw 23,115 models find new homes, more than 33,000 examples of the Honda Prologue made it to buyer driveways. That’s a pretty hefty difference, no matter what way you cut it.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe 2025 Chevrolet Blazer EV is far from the worst EV in the industry, but the fact it has a twin wearing the Honda badge, complete with consumer-favorite tech, is definitely a downside. Take a ride in the Honda Prologue before you bring home a Chevrolet Blazer EV.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLove reading Autoblog? Sign up for our weekly newsletter to get exclusive articles, insider insights, and the latest updates delivered right to your inbox. \u003ca href=\"https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.autoblog.com%2Fnewsletter%3Fplacement%3DAboveGlobalNavLeft\u0026amp;data=05%7C02%7C%7Cffd0f783f9e04f83a11208dd42455d47%7C84df9e7fe9f640afb435aaaaaaaaaaaa%7C1%7C0%7C638739587858527058%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C\u0026amp;sdata=ZCSKIqI3Sa8SF1vr4aSdmNL%2B3dkLG%2F%2FWzHTX%2Brv1fL4%3D\u0026amp;reserved=0\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eClick here to sign up now!\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/2025-vw-taos-4-pros-vs-2-cons-you-need-to-know\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
